data.chText: （尤指对个人或小组的）教学，讲授，指导
data.enText: the act of teaching sth, especially to one person or to people in small groups
She received private tuition in French.
the money that you pay to be taught, especially in a college or university

simple_means.memory_skill: tuit 保护；指导，教育 + ion 表名词 → 受教育的费用 → 学费

means: (尤指对个人或小组的)教学，讲授，指导

tr: teaching pupils individually (usually by a tutor hired privately)
a fee paid for instruction (especially for higher education)
example: tuition and room and board were more than $25,000

value.def: If you are given tuition in a particular subject, you are taught about that subject.

example.ex: The courses will give the beginner personal tuition in all types of outdoor photography.
example.tran: 该课程将为初学者一对一地讲授各种户外摄影技巧。

value.def: You can use tuition to refer to the amount of money that you have to pay for being taught particular subjects, especially in a university, college, or private school.

example.ex: Angela's $7,000 tuition at University this year will be paid for with scholarships.
example.tran: 安杰拉将用奖学金支付今年 7,000 美元的大学学费。

value.tran: （尤指大专院校或私立学校的）学费

trans: 学费减免；免学费；减免学费；免除学费；全免膏火

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to protect or guard, to guide or teach 保护；指导, 教育
rootsaffixes.title: tut, tuit

partsOfSpeech.dec: as 加强 + tut 保护；指导，教育 + e → 加强教育才能变机敏 → 机敏的
in 不 + tuit 保护；指导，教育 + ion 表名词 → 不用教导就有的〔感觉〕→ 直觉
in 不 + tuit 保护；指导，教育 + ive 有…性质的 → 直觉的
tuit 保护；指导，教育 + ion 表名词 → 受教育的费用 → 学费
tutel〔= tut〕保护；指导，教育 + age 表行为 → 保护；教育
tut 保护；指导，教育 + or 表人 → 保护人；导师
tutor 保护人；导师 + ial 具有…的，属于…的 → 私人教师的
un 无 + tutor 保护人；导师 + ed 表形容词 → 未受教育的
